						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="italic">Hero-stone in front of the Hanumān temple.</hi></p>						

						<p>This damaged inscription seems to refer to the setting up of (the hero-stone depicting) <hi rend="bold">Timmayya-Nāyaka</hi> by <hi rend="bold">Ammajayya-Nāyaka.</hi> Timmayya died in a fight when <hi rend="bold">Kadiramaṇḍalage</hi> was attacked.</p>						

						<p>The record is dated in the cyclic year <hi rend="bold">[Vi]shu, Vaiśākha śu.</hi> The <hi rend="bold">Śaka</hi> year and other deatils of the date are not given. The characters belong to about the <hi rend="bold">15th century A.D.</hi> </p>						

						</summary>
					</msContents>
